<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Use the screenshot utility.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Garbonzo Darkbean">Garbonzo Darkbean</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:44 a.m. 16/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Use the screenshot utility.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1488" TARGET=_self>Idea's on what is needed to make the PvP server float.</A> (Ambassator Vilar)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> A easy way to file complaint about players violating the Rules

<BR>&gt; Of Conduct.
<BR>&gt; playing a Dark Elf in the beta I heard a fair bit (not nearly UO
<BR>&gt; levels though) of "U
<BR>&gt; Niggaz! Come to the pass so I can slap your black bitch
<BR>&gt; ass". Totally unacceptable but if
<BR>&gt; we send in a petition the guide who shows up has to hang around
<BR>&gt; hoping its repeated.
<BR>&gt; Guides do not have time for that. There should be a way to file
<BR>&gt; a complaint along with a
<BR>&gt; log of all the resent /tells, /shouts and /emotes I recieved.
<P>Just snap a screenshot of the text with the "-" key, and email it to Verant. I guarantee you they are itching for a reason to ban morons like this from their game, and if you provide them with ample evidence (it's hard to deny a screenshot, especially if you get a few of the same person doing/saying similar things) then Verant will have the ammunition they need.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
